      "title": "Psychological testing. Design, analysis, and use",
      "abstract": "Using This Book. I. TEST DESIGN. 1. Introduction to Psychological Testing. 2. Test Development. 3. Ability Tests. 4. Personality Tests and Rating Tests. II. TEST ANALYSIS. 5. Working with Scores. 6. Reliability Analyses. 7. Validity Analyses. 8. Item Analysis. III. TEST USE. 9. Testing in Educational Settings. 10. Testing in Clinical Settings. 11. Testing in Counseling Settings. 12. Testing in the Workplace. Glossary. Appendices. Answers To Practice Problems. References. Index."
